As a successful, innovative company, Frequentis offers employees an inspiring
working environment: This is achieved with a culture of openness, diversity,
and appreciation, as well as with motivating career development opportunities
and equal promotion of all genders.

** Position Purpose **

The Systems Engineer provides technical engineering expertise in the
development and implementation of Control Centre communications and
information systems.

** Main Tasks **

  * Perform requirements analysis and engineering design 
  * System installation, deployment, configuration and integration 
  * Testing and error identification during integration of software into customer environment 
  * Develop technical knowledge of Frequentisâ€™ existing products and processes 
  * Creation of technical documentation of systems and their interfaces 
  * Creation of system/subsystem specification artefacts 
  * Acceptance of internal and external deliverables for assigned work packages 

The above lists are not exhaustive, and the role may evolve to meet the
overall objectives of the company.

** Training **

Specialist Frequentis system training will be provided for products related to
the role from the Frequentis product portfolio.

** Experience and Skills **

  * At least 5 years of project systems experience, ideally in safety critical, control centre design, integration and verification (desirable). 
  * Technical education for software solutions, communication solutions, traceability processes and test engineering 
  * Hands-on experience with at least one of; specification, system installation, integration, and testing. 
  * Ability to build and work in the mission-critical safety environments 

** Qualifications **

  * A relevant University qualification in Engineering, Software, Information Technology or related discipline. 

We are committed to building a workforce that reflects the diverse society in
which we live and work. We recognise the increasing importance of flexible
work arrangements and family friendly work practices to enable and maintain a
diverse, adaptive and high performing workforce.

